Chelsea defeated Tottenham 1-0 to qualify for the League Cup final in England. with a 3-0 goals aggregate.
Antonio Rudiger sailed Chelsea into victory with a header that gave the team the winning goal of the match in the first half of the game. Chelsea had won the first leg 2-0 last week, sealing the victory and qualification of the League Cup final with a 1-0 win on Wednesday.
The final match will be between Chelsea and either Liverpool or Arsenal on February 27 at Wembley.
This victory improves the record of Thomas Tuchel qualifying Chelsea for the third finals since becoming Chelsea Coach in January 2020 after the exit of Frank Lampard.
